<sec>
<st>
 Features </st>
<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Transactions: if database update fails in the middle of a transaction, the database is guaranteed to remain in a consistent state.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Simultaneous search and update, with new documents being immediately visible.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Support for large databases: Xapian has been proven to be scalable to hundreds of millions of documents.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Accurate probabilistic ranking: more relevant documents are listed first.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Phrase and proximity searching.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Relevance feedback, which improves ranking and can expand a query, find related documents, categorise documents etc.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Structured Boolean queries, e.g. "race AND condition NOT horse"</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Wildcard search, e.g. "wiki*"</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Spelling correction</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 Omega, a packaged solution for adding a search engine to a web site or intranet. Omega can easily be extended and adapted to fit changing requirements.</entry>
</list>
</p>

